<h1>@HI{{na}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{na}}</strong>.
<li> <strong>@HI{{naa}}</strong>.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{na}}</strong> is a sentence ending particle with a number of uses.
</p>

<p>
Some uses of <strong>@HI{{na}}</strong> are most often used by men:
<ul>
<li> indicates emotion
<li> asks for agreement
<li> indicates <a href="grammar-verb-use-of-imperative-prohibitive.html">prohibition</a>
</ul>
</p>

<p>
Some uses of <strong>@HI{{na}}</strong> can be used by either men or women:
<ul>
<li> softens the effect of an assertion
<li> softens a request or a command
</ul>
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kireina@KJ{{star}}da<strong>naa</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What a beautiful star!
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{car}}ha@KJ{{new^car}}da yo<strong>na</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That's a new car I bet.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mouano@KT{{ba-}}ni@KJ{{going}}<strong>na</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Don't go to that bar again.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{reflect^brush-stroke}}hayokunakatta<strong>na</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That film wasn't very good.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{turn*into^rice*field}}made@KJ{{going}}ttekudasai<strong>na</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Narita ariport, if you please. <em>(used by a woman)</em>
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{bright^day^invariably}}zu@KJ{{come}}ru<strong>na</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Be sure to come tomorrow. <em>(used by a man)</em>
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

